not fail in the gradle checks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Instantiate necessary classes for quiz function
commitResults.messageBody:
The SubjectQuiz and TopicQuiz classes instantiates the
quiz feature for the topic or subject which it is called for.

The Result class checks the result that the user had obtained for the quiz.
The ResultList class stores all of the results from the quizzes for each subject/topic.

commitResults.messageTitle: Integrating the quiz and result features of a subject into the application
commitResults.messageBody:
The QuizSubjectCommand.class instantiated the quiz feature while
the ResultSubjectCommand.class instantiates the results feature
for the subject.

commitResults.messageTitle: Integrating the quiz and result features of a topic into the application
commitResults.messageBody:
The QuizTopicCommand.class instantiated the quiz feature while
the ResultTopicCommand.class instantiates the results feature
for the topic.

These commands are added instantiated in the TopicParser.java
class.

commitResults.messageBody:

commitResults.messageTitle: Update the storage classes to read the date and time of the event
commitResults.messageBody:
The Storage class and the TaskList classes  now
reads the date and time of the event in the correct format.
This is essential to save the data to an external file
and to load it when the application starts.

The StorageTest class was modified to accomodate these
changes.

commitResults.messageBody:
The code now reads the date and time of the
event/deadline task to be added.

An exception is thrown if the user enters
the date and time in the wrong format.

within a week to the user.
